knew you were gone?

250
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:42,416
Oh, just shut up!

251
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:44,125
That's none of
your concern, human!

252
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:46,791
I guess,
but you don't have to yell.

253
00:14:50,916 --> 00:14:51,958
[MASTER]
This way.

254
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:53,291
[ITTAN MOMEN 3A]
There she is!

255
00:14:53,375 --> 00:14:54,958
[ITTAN MOMEN 3B] We knew
you'd come to the harbor.

256
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:56,083
[ITTAN MOMEN 3C]
Tenjin-ya!

257
00:14:56,166 --> 00:14:58,583
How nice,
the ittan-momen tracked us.

258
00:14:58,666 --> 00:15:00,750
Wait, I thought
ittan-momen were fluttery,

259
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,125
cloth-like spirits.

260
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:04,041
Every <i>ayakashi</i> is different.

261
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:06,125
They each have
their own human form.

262
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,750
Suzuran, go ahead
and board the ship.

263
00:15:09,833 --> 00:15:11,375
[SUZURAN]
Right.

264
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,833
[ITTAN MOMEN 3A]
Hey, hold it right there!

265
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:16,125
[ITTAN MOMEN 3B]
Young Master!

266
00:15:19,666 --> 00:15:22,333
Well, well.
It's been quite a while,

267
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:25,250
Master innkeeper of Tenjin-ya.

268
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,500
I would like you
to hand over Suzuran, please.

269
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:32,000
As heir to the Yahata-ya,
I own her.

270
00:15:32,083 --> 00:15:33,666
I've already gone
through the formalities

271
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:35,916
and cleared
the bureaucratic hurdles.

272
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,375
What a nice surprise.

273
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:39,500
It's Yahata-ya's young master.

274
00:15:39,583 --> 00:15:41,000
About Suzuran,

275
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:43,375
she's our front desk
manager's younger sister.

276
00:15:43,458 --> 00:15:45,250
I thought a little
sibling bonding time

277
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:46,500
was in order for them.

278
00:15:46,583 --> 00:15:49,750
So we're taking her back
to Tenjin-ya for a bit.

279
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:52,041
Lies! How dare you interfere?!

280
00:15:52,125 --> 00:15:53,666
Besides, Young Master.

281
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:54,875
I am under the impression

282
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:56,958
that Suzuran
doesn't even like you.

283
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,708
So this idea of forcing her
to marry you,

284
00:15:59,791 --> 00:16:02,708
it seems a little selfish
on your part, wouldn't you say?

285
00:16:02,791 --> 00:16:04,708
Hey. Look who's
talking, mister!

286
00:16:04,791 --> 00:16:07,541
I never!
What an egregious affront!

287
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:10,708
You will regret this.
I should declare war.

288
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:15,291
Why are they leaving
without us onboard?

289
00:16:15,375 --> 00:16:16,916
[TANNOSUKE]
Stop them!

290
00:16:17,916 --> 00:16:19,375
[TANNOSUKE]
And, fire!

291
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:40,125
Ah! Oh, no! Arrows!

292
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:50,708
My, you decided
to protect me? How kind!

293
00:16:50,791 --> 00:16:54,833
[AOI] No, it was self-defense.
This thing is incredible!

294
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,000
[ITTAN MOMEN 3A]
What? The tengu treasure fan?

295
00:16:57,083 --> 00:16:59,083
[ITTAN MOMEN 3B] Yeah, but
why does that girl have it?

296
00:16:59,166 --> 00:17:00,541
Hey! You, there!

297
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:02,416
Just who in the world are you?

298
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:04,333
Are you a tengu?

299
00:17:04,416 --> 00:17:07,375
What? Why should I
tell you anything?

300
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:11,958
This girl is
Shiro Tsubaki's granddaughter,

301
00:17:12,041 --> 00:17:15,875
Aoi Tsubaki. She also happens
to be my fiancée,

302
00:17:15,958 --> 00:17:17,166
just so you know.

303
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:20,041
Did you just say Shiro
Tsubaki's granddaughter?

304
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:22,875
What? And she's
going to marry you?

305
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:24,458
Absurd!

306
00:17:31,041 --> 00:17:32,583
[AOI gasps]

307
00:17:44,375 --> 00:17:46,458
[ITTAN MOMEN 3A]
This is an absolute tragedy!

308
00:17:46,541 --> 00:17:48,000
[ITTAN MOMEN 3B] It's the end
of the hidden realm!

309
00:17:48,083 --> 00:17:50,125
[ITTAN MOMEN 3C]
Awful ogre bride of Tenjin-ya!

310
00:17:50,208 --> 00:17:52,333
What? What did he call me?

311
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:54,041
[ITTAN MOMEN]
Ogre bride! Ogre bride!

312
00:17:54,125 --> 00:17:55,083
Ogre bride!

313
00:17:55,166 --> 00:17:57,583
Hey, I don't like that name!

314
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,500
Well, I'm back.

315
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:30,500
Suzuran?

316
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,000
Big brother!

317
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:38,458
Hey, what are you doing here?

318
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:41,541
The master just saved me
from a terrible fate!

319
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:45,250
I would've-- I would've--
Oh, Brother!

320
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:46,416
[sobbing]

321
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,250
What? What happened to you?

322
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:49,916
Breathe!

323
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,583
[HOSTESS]
O-Ryo!

324
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:54,375
[HOSTESS]
Where've you been?

325
00:18:54,458 --> 00:18:56,125
You disappeared
without permission--

326
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:57,791
at a very busy time!

327
00:18:57,875 --> 00:19:00,708
[O-RYO] I know.
I'm incredibly sorry, Mistress.

328
00:19:00,791 --> 00:19:02,416
This behavior's intolerable.

329
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:04,208
I assumed you had
great potential,

330
00:19:04,291 --> 00:19:07,291
which is why I recommended
that you become young hostess.

331
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:10,250
And yet you repay my kindness
by disgracing me?

332
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:13,458
Um, I was just-- I was--

333
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:15,416
O-Ryo, I commanded you

334
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,833
to look after
Tenjin-ya while I was gone.

335
00:19:17,916 --> 00:19:19,958
Why did you choose
to disobey me?

336
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:23,625
I'm-- I'm so sorry.

337
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:26,041
I was very worried
about you, Master.

338
00:19:26,125 --> 00:19:30,166
Enough. Your sweet, repentant
act won't work on me this time.

339
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:32,375
I saw what you did to Aoi.

340
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:33,625
[gasps]

341
00:19:33,708 --> 00:19:35,250
It appears you're still

342
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,208
far too immature
to be young hostess.

343
00:19:37,291 --> 00:19:38,541
[O-RYO cries]

344
00:19:38,625 --> 00:19:41,208
[MASTER] I order you to be
confined to your room,

345
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,291
until your punishment
is decided.

346
00:19:44,625 --> 00:19:46,375
[O-RYO cries]

347
00:19:52,666 --> 00:19:53,833
[AOI]
I still can't believe

348
00:19:53,916 --> 00:19:55,958
how relaxed
this place makes me!

349
00:19:57,750 --> 00:20:00,375
[GINJI]
Welcome back, Chef Aoi.

350
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:02,541
How did you enjoy
your trip to Youto?

351
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:04,375
Tell me, were you able
to have a good time

352
00:20:04,458 --> 00:20:06,625
taking in all the sights
there with the Master?

353
00:20:06,708 --> 00:20:08,583
Did I "have a good time"?

354
00:20:08,666 --> 00:20:11,000
U-Um, the whole trip
was chaos, honestly.

355
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:12,500
Oh?

356
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,500
[GINJI]
I see what you mean.

357
00:20:15,583 --> 00:20:17,625
You certainly had
your hands full!

358
00:20:17,708 --> 00:20:19,916
All right, what is all of this?

359
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,875
Well, I figured we should
start planning the menu

360
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:26,041
for your new restaurant.
These will help us brainstorm.

361
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:27,208
Oh, good call.

362
00:20:27,291 --> 00:20:29,041
We have to come up
with a wide variety

363
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:31,833
of dishes to appeal
to all kinds of <i>ayakashi.</i>

364
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,125
Here. I want you to try this.

365
00:20:37,208 --> 00:20:38,666
Is it alcohol?

366
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:41,125
[GINJI]
No, it's fruit juice.

367
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:45,041
Delicious! It's sweet
cherry juice, right?

368
00:20:45,125 --> 00:20:48,250
Cherries that have been simmered
with a bit of sugar mixed in.

369
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:49,583
You're exactly right.

370
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:52,208
We're in
a cherry-growing district.

371
00:20:52,291 --> 00:20:55,041
This is one of the most popular
items in our gift shop,

372
00:20:55,125 --> 00:20:56,833
but some of the bottle labels
got messed up

373
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,291
in the fight with the tengu,

374
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,666
so I asked if we could have
some of the damaged ones.

375
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:04,208
Spectacular! I'd like to make
some kind of dessert using this.

376
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:05,875
Yes. Great!

377
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:08,916
I wonder what else we can
put on our new menu.

378
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,500
The dishes served
in the main building

379
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:12,375
are all more traditional fare.

380
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:15,625
So in our place, let's focus on
dishes from the apparent realm.

381
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:18,500
Ones mostly still unknown
to us here in the hidden realm.

382
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:21,000
Uh, you'll have to help me
learn what those are.

383
00:21:21,083 --> 00:21:24,291
Right. The rice omelette
you made me, for example.

384
00:21:24,375 --> 00:21:26,041
I know it'd be a hit!

385
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:27,791
I'm happy you liked it.

386
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:29,541
Anything else you can think of?

387
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:31,416
Let me see...

388
00:21:31,500 --> 00:21:34,041
Well, curry and rice, maybe?

389
00:21:34,125 --> 00:21:36,458
I know that dish
is your favorite.

390
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:39,166
Curry, huh?
We could add a little fruit

391
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:41,666
to make it sweet enough
for the <i>ayakashi</i> palate.

392
00:21:41,750 --> 00:21:45,291
Good idea! I can't wait
to help experiment!

393
00:21:45,375 --> 00:21:49,208
All right, I'd better get back
to my official work now.

394
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:53,666
Ginji, thank you
for all your help.

395
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,166
Heh.

396
00:21:58,250 --> 00:22:00,875
He's really into all this.

397
00:22:00,958 --> 00:22:04,208
Hold on. How did Ginji even
know I liked curry and rice.

398
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:05,208
That's odd.

399
00:22:05,291 --> 00:22:07,958
[KASUGA]
Hey! Miss Aoi!

400
00:22:08,041 --> 00:22:10,791
[AOI]
Kasuga? Hey. What's going on?

401
00:22:10,875 --> 00:22:13,291
[KASUGA]
Miss O-Ryo collapsed!

402
00:23:48,375 --> 00:23:50,875
[CHIBI] The hidden realm can
be just as tough a place

403
00:23:50,958 --> 00:23:52,375
as the apparent realm, huh?

404
00:23:52,458 --> 00:23:53,791
But it's okay, don't worry!

405
00:23:53,875 --> 00:23:56,208
I bet if you give the Snow Woman
some cucumber pieces,

406
00:23:56,291 --> 00:23:57,791
she'll be your friend too!

